Andy s Home Page If it ain t real fun  it ain t real science andy s page introduction introduction teaching teaching students students current projects current projects past projects past projects publications publications grants grants experience experience fun stuff fun stuff evl evl CS CS Engineering Engineering UIC UIC Dr  Andrew Johnson is Director of Research at the Electronic Visualization Laboratory and an Associate Professor of Computer Science at the University of Illinois at Chicago  nHis research and teaching focus on interaction and collaboration using advanced visualization displays and the application of those displays to enhance discovery and learning News spring      n This term I will be teaching CS     Visualization and Visual Analytics I n CS     Visualization and Visual Analytics I fall      n This term I am teaching Virtual and Augmented Reality again  now in the new Continuum space  and the special topics course has now been approved as a regular course  n   Virtual and Augmented Reality summer      n  evl staff and students  including   CS undergrads  are spending the summer installing and testing the core of the Continuum display and sensor systems  n spring      n This term I am teaching CS     Visualization and Visual Analytics I n CS     Visualization and Visual Analytics I  n   Remodeling has finished on our new Continuum space so now we get to start adding in the fun stuff n    n   I  along with Bob and Max  got to meet Ivan Sutherland n   fall      n This term I am teaching a new     level course on Virtual and Augmented Reality that will act as a more practical introduction to the field compared to the graduate level Virtual Reality course that I have taught for the last    years  n   Virtual and Augmented Reality Victor successfully defended his PhD dissertation   Supporting Navigation with a Torso Wearable Tactile Display   on December   th Our CAVE  US patent was finally granted #            System and methods for visualizing infor